# Claude Office Assistant — How It Works

## The Big Picture

```
Your Browser  ←→  Flask Server (Python)  ←→  Claude API (Anthropic)
    ↕                    ↕
 frontend/           backend/
 (HTML/JS/CSS)       (Python files)
```

When you type a message → browser sends it to Flask → Flask calls Claude → 
Claude streams the reply back → you see it word by word.

---

## 1. How a Message Gets Answered

```
You type "Write me a Python script"
         ↓
app.js detects keyword "python" → task = "coding"
         ↓
Flask /api/conversations/<id>/stream called (POST)
         ↓
backend checks budget (has $150 left? yes)
         ↓
memory_store injects your saved facts into system prompt
         ↓
model_router picks Claude Sonnet (because task = "coding")
         ↓
conversation_store adds last 20 messages for context
         ↓
Anthropic API streams response token by token
         ↓
Flask yields each chunk as SSE: data: {"type":"text","text":"..."}
         ↓
app.js reads the stream word by word → updates the DOM live
         ↓
When done: saves to conversations.json, usage.json, updates budget
```

---

## 2. File Uploads — How They Work

```
You click 📎 or drag a file onto the page
         ↓
app.js sends file to POST /api/upload
         ↓
file_processor.py reads the file:
  - .jpg/.png/.gif/.webp → base64 encode → type: "image"
  - .pdf  → pypdf extracts all text pages → type: "document"
  - .docx → python-docx reads paragraphs → type: "document"
  - .xlsx → openpyxl reads all sheets → type: "document"
  - .py/.js/.ts/.json/etc. → read as plain text → type: "document"
         ↓
File chip appears in the UI (with icon, name, size)
         ↓
When you hit Send:
  - Images go as vision content blocks (Claude literally sees the image)
  - Documents get injected into the message text with the content
  - Claude reads and responds to both
```

---

## 3. Memory — How It Works

```
You open 🧠 Memory → type "I prefer Python over JavaScript" → Save
         ↓
POST /api/memory/<user_id>
         ↓
memory_store.py saves to logs/memories.json:
{
  "abhinav": [
    { "id": "mem_abc123", "content": "I prefer Python over JavaScript",
      "source": "manual", "created_at": "2026-05-01T..." }
  ]
}
         ↓
EVERY future message you send:
  memory_store.format_for_prompt("abhinav") returns:
  "\n\n[User Memory]\n- I prefer Python over JavaScript\n"
         ↓
This gets appended to Claude's system prompt EVERY time
→ Claude always knows your preferences without you repeating them
```

---

## 4. Conversation History — How It Works

```
You send message 1 → saved to conversations.json
You send message 2 → saved to conversations.json
You send message 3 → Claude gets messages [1, 2, 3] as context
         ↓
conversation_store.get_context_messages(conv_id)
→ returns last 20 messages [{role:"user",content:"..."}, ...]
→ sent to Claude as multi-turn conversation history
→ Claude reads EVERYTHING and responds in full context
         ↓
Conversation title: auto-generated from your first message
Grouped in sidebar: TODAY / YESTERDAY / EARLIER
Persisted: closing the browser and reopening shows same conversations
```

---

## 5. Smart Model Routing (Cost Saving)

```
Your message → keyword scan → pick model

Keywords containing:              → Model Used
"code", "python", "javascript",   → Claude Sonnet (smarter, costs more)
"debug", "function", "html",
"css", "website", "design"

"slide", "presentation",          → Claude Sonnet
"deck", "powerpoint"

Everything else                   → Claude Haiku (faster, cheaper)
"write", "email", "caption",
"explain", "help", general chat
```

---

## 6. All the Files Explained

### Backend (Python — runs the server)

| File | What it does |
|------|-------------|
| `app.py` | The main server — all API routes, serves the frontend |
| `conversation_store.py` | Saves/loads all conversations to `logs/conversations.json` |
| `memory_store.py` | Saves/loads user memories to `logs/memories.json` |
| `file_processor.py` | Reads images, PDFs, DOCX, XLSX, code files |
| `model_router.py` | Decides Haiku vs Sonnet based on task type |
| `budget_tracker.py` | Tracks monthly spend, blocks calls if over $150 |
| `requirements.txt` | All Python packages needed |

### Frontend (HTML/JS/CSS — what you see)

| File | What it does |
|------|-------------|
| `index.html` | Main chat UI — sidebar, chat view, file chips, memory panel |
| `app.js` | All frontend logic — streaming, file upload, memory CRUD, sending messages |
| `style.css` | Complete dark-mode design system |
| `dashboard.html` | Cost & usage monitoring — see all API calls, spend per user |
| `html-generator.html` | AI-powered HTML page builder tool |
| `presentation.html` | Slide deck creator tool |

### Config & Data

| File | What it does |
|------|-------------|
| `config/.env` | **API key goes here** + Flask settings, budget limit |
| `config/employees.json` | The employee profiles shown in the picker modal |
| `logs/conversations.json` | All conversations (auto-created) |
| `logs/memories.json` | All user memories (auto-created) |
| `logs/usage.json` | Every API call logged with cost + tokens (auto-created) |

---

## 7. What Happens When You Run `bash start.sh`

```
1. Checks if ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is set → warns if not
2. Creates Python virtual environment (venv/) if not exists
3. Installs all packages from requirements.txt
4. Starts Flask on http://localhost:5000
5. Auto-opens browser to http://localhost:5000
6. Flask now serves BOTH the frontend AND the API
   - GET  /              → serves index.html
   - GET  /dashboard.html → serves dashboard.html
   - POST /api/...       → handles all API calls
```

---

## 8. API Routes (What the Backend Exposes)

| Method | Route | What it does |
|--------|-------|-------------|
| GET | `/api/health` | Check server is alive |
| GET | `/api/employees` | List employee profiles |
| GET | `/api/budget` | Current month spend |
| POST | `/api/conversations` | Create new conversation |
| GET | `/api/conversations` | List all conversations for a user |
| POST | `/api/conversations/<id>/stream` | **Send message, get streaming reply** |
| DELETE | `/api/conversations/<id>` | Delete a conversation |
| PATCH | `/api/conversations/<id>/title` | Rename conversation |
| POST | `/api/upload` | Upload and process a file |
| GET | `/api/memory/<user_id>` | Get user's memories |
| POST | `/api/memory/<user_id>` | Add a memory |
| DELETE | `/api/memory/<user_id>/<mem_id>` | Delete a memory |

---

## 9. What Makes It Different From Plain Claude.ai

| Feature | Claude.ai | This System |
|---------|-----------|-------------|
| Multi-user profiles | ❌ (1 account) | ✅ Multiple employees |
| Budget tracking | ❌ | ✅ $150/month cap with real-time tracking |
| Cost per message | ❌ | ✅ Shows exact cost (e.g. $0.00023) |
| Model auto-routing | ❌ | ✅ Haiku vs Sonnet based on task |
| Usage dashboard | ❌ | ✅ Full analytics page |
| Presentation tool | ❌ | ✅ Built-in slide creator |
| HTML generator | ❌ | ✅ AI web page builder |
| WhatsApp bot | ❌ | ✅ Twilio/Interakt integration |
| Self-hosted | ❌ | ✅ Your data, your server |
